{"title_page": "Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics", "text_new": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Freestyle skiing\n|games = 2014 Winter\n| image       = [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Aerials), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Halfpipe), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Moguls), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Ski Cross), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Slopestyle), Sochi 2014.png|90px]]\n| caption     = Pictograms for Aerials, Halfpipe, Moguls, Ski Cross, and Slopestyle.\n|venue = [[Rosa Khutor Extreme Park]], [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]], [[Russia]]\n|dates = 6\u201321 February 2014\n|competitors = 277\n|nations = 30\n|prev = [[Freestyle skiing at the 2010 Winter Olympics|2010]]\n|next = [[Freestyle skiing at the 2018 Winter Olympics|2018]]\n}}\n{{Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics}}\n'''[[Freestyle skiing at the Winter Olympics|Freestyle skiing]] at the [[2014 Winter Olympics]]''' was held at the [[Rosa Khutor Extreme Park]] near [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]], [[Russia]]. The ten events took place between 6\u201321 February 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/games/places/objects/mountain/snowboard/ |title=Rosa Khutor Extreme Park |publisher=[[SOOC]] |accessdate=10 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2011 the [[International Olympic Committee]] approved the addition of the halfpipe event for both, men and women.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ski halfpipe approved for 2014 Olympics |first=Olivia |last=Dwyer |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/action/freeskiing/news/story?id=6273652 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=6 April 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref> In July 2011, [[slopestyle]] was also added to the program, therefore a total of four new events were added to the freestyle skiing program.<ref>{{cite news |title=Slopestyle approved for 2014 Olympics |first=Olivia |last=Dwyer |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/action/news/story?id=6662007 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=4 July 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Competition schedule==\n[[File:Rosa Khutor.jpg|300px|thumb|Rosa Khutor Alpine Resort, the venue for freestyle skiing]]\nThe following is the competition schedule for all ten events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/freestyle-skiing-schedule-and-results |title=Freestyle Skiing Schedule and Results |publisher=[[SOOC]] |accessdate=11 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n<small>All times are ([[Moscow Time|UTC+4]]).</small>\n{| class=wikitable\n! Date !! Time !! Event\n|-\n| 6 February || 18:00 || Women's moguls qualification\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 8 February || 18:00 || Women's moguls qualification 2\n|-\n| 22:00 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Women's moguls final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 10 February || 18:00 ||Men's moguls qualification\n|-\n| 22:00 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Men's moguls final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 11 February || 10:00 ||Women's slopestyle qualification\n|-\n| 13:00 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Women's slopestyle final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 13 February || 10:15 ||Men's slopestyle qualification\n|-\n| 13:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Men's slopestyle final'''\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 14 February || 17:45 ||Women's aerials qualification\n|-\n| 21:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Women's aerials final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 17 February || 17:45 ||Men's aerials qualification\n|-\n| 21:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Men's aerials final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 18 February || 17:45 ||Men's halfpipe qualification\n|-\n| 21:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Men's halfpipe final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=4| 20 February || 11:45 ||Men's ski cross qualification\n|-\n| 13:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Men's ski cross finals'''\n|-\n| 18:30 ||Women's halfpipe qualification\n|-\n| 21:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Women's halfpipe final'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 21 February || 11:45 ||Women's ski cross qualification\n|-\n| 13:30 ||style=background:lemonchiffon|'''Women's ski cross finals'''\n|}\n\n==Medal summary==\n\n===Medal table===\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = RUS\n | flag_template  = flagIOCteam\n | event          = 2014 Winter\n | team           = \n | gold_CAN = 4 | silver_CAN = 4 | bronze_CAN = 1\n | gold_USA = 3 | silver_USA = 2 | bronze_USA = 2\n | gold_BLR = 2 | silver_BLR = 0 | bronze_BLR = 0\n | gold_FRA = 1 | silver_FRA = 2 | bronze_FRA = 2\n | gold_AUS = 0 | silver_AUS = 1 | bronze_AUS = 1\n | gold_CHN = 0 | silver_CHN = 1 | bronze_CHN = 1\n | gold_JPN = 0 | silver_JPN = 0 | bronze_JPN = 1\n | gold_RUS = 0 | silver_RUS = 0 | bronze_RUS = 1 | host_RUS = yes \n | gold_SWE = 0 | silver_SWE = 0 | bronze_SWE = 1\n}}\n\n===Men's events===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|columns=2}}\n|-\n|aerials<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's aerials}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Anton Kushnir]]|BLR|2014 Winter}} || 134.50\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[David Morris (skier)|David Morris]]|AUS|2014 Winter}} || 110.41\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Jia Zongyang]]|CHN|2014 Winter}} || 95.06\n|-\n|halfpipe<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's halfpipe}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[David Wise (freestyle skier)|David Wise]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 92.00\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mike Riddle]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 90.60\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Kevin Rolland]]|FRA|2014 Winter}} || 88.60\n|-\n|moguls<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's moguls}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Alexandre Bilodeau]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 26.31\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mika\u00ebl Kingsbury]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 24.71\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Alexandr Smyshlyaev]]|RUS|2014 Winter}} || 24.34\n|-\n|slopestyle<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's slopestyle}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Joss Christensen]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 95.80\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Gus Kenworthy]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 93.60\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Nick Goepper]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 92.40\n|-\n|ski cross<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's ski cross}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Jean-Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chapuis]]|FRA|2014 Winter}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Arnaud Bovolenta]]|FRA|2014 Winter}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Jonathan Midol]]|FRA|2014 Winter}}\n|}\n\n===Women's events===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|columns=2}}\n|-\n|aerials<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's aerials}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Alla Tsuper]]|BLR|2014 Winter}}|| 98.01\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Xu Mengtao]]|CHN|2014 Winter}}||83.50\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Lydia Lassila]]|AUS|2014 Winter}}|| 72.12\n|-\n|halfpipe<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's halfpipe}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Maddie Bowman]]|USA|2014 Winter}}|| 89.00\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Marie Martinod]]|FRA|2014 Winter}}|| 85.40\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Ayana Onozuka]]|JPN|2014 Winter}}|| 83.20\n|-\n|moguls<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's moguls}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Justine Dufour-Lapointe]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 22.44\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Chlo\u00e9 Dufour-Lapointe]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 21.66\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Hannah Kearney]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 21.49\n|-\n|slopestyle<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's slopestyle}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Dara Howell]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 94.20\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Devin Logan]]|USA|2014 Winter}} || 85.40\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Kim Lamarre]]|CAN|2014 Winter}} || 85.00\n|-\n|ski cross<br />{{DetailsLink|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's ski cross}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Marielle Thompson]]|CAN|2014 Winter}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Kelsey Serwa]]|CAN|2014 Winter}}\n|colspan=2|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Anna Holmlund]]|SWE|2014 Winter}}\n|}\n\n==Qualification==\n{{main|Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Qualification}}\nA maximum of 282 quota spots were available to athletes to compete at the games. A maximum of 26 athletes could be entered by a [[National Olympic Committee]], with a maximum of 14 men or 14 women. The five different events had different quota amounts allocated to them.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://data.fis-ski.com/media/olympic-games/sochi2014-18-09-2012-qualification-system-fis-english.pdf |title=Qualification Systems for XXII Olympic Winter Games, Sochi 2014 |date=December 2011 |publisher=[[International Ski Federation]] |accessdate=10 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Participating nations==\n276 athletes from 30 nations participated, with number of athletes in parentheses. Four nations, [[Belgium at the 2014 Winter Olympics|Belgium]], [[Brazil at the 2014 Winter Olympics|Brazil]], [[British Virgin Islands at the 2014 Winter Olympics|The British Virgin Islands]] and [[Chile at the 2014 Winter Olympics|Chile]] made their Olympic debuts in the sport. [[Paraguay at the 2014 Winter Olympics|Paraguay]] made its first appearance at the [[Winter Olympics]], with its only athlete competing in [[freestyle skiing]].<ref name=\"a\">{{cite news |last=Vincent |first=Gordon |date=6 December 2013 |title=Winchester's Marino is first Winter Olympian from Paraguay |url=http://homenewshere.com/middlesex_east/article_f432c936-5cf1-11e3-87af-0019bb2963f4.html |newspaper=Middlesex East |accessdate=27 December 2013 }}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin|width=100%}}\n{{col-1-of-3}}\n* {{flagIOC|AUS|2014 Winter|21}}\n* {{flagIOC|AUT|2014 Winter|11}}\n* {{flagIOC|BLR|2014 Winter|6}}\n* {{flagIOC|BEL|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|BRA|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|IVB|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|CAN|2014 Winter|26}}\n* {{flagIOC|CHI|2014 Winter|2}}\n* {{flagIOC|CHN|2014 Winter|9}}\n* {{flagIOC|CZE|2014 Winter|6}}\n{{col-2-of-3}}\n* {{flagIOC|FIN|2014 Winter|9}}\n* {{flagIOC|FRA|2014 Winter|21}}\n* {{flagIOC|GER|2014 Winter|10}}\n* {{flagIOC|GBR|2014 Winter|6}}\n* {{flagIOC|ITA|2014 Winter|4}}\n* {{flagIOC|JPN|2014 Winter|10}}\n* {{flagIOC|KAZ|2014 Winter|8}}\n* {{flagIOC|NZL|2014 Winter|8}}\n* {{flagIOC|NOR|2014 Winter|11}}\n* {{flagIOC|PAR|2014 Winter|1}}\n{{col-3-of-3}}\n* {{flagIOC|POL|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|RUS|2014 Winter|26}}\n* {{flagIOC|SVK|2014 Winter|2}}\n* {{flagIOC|SLO|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|KOR|2014 Winter|5}}\n* {{flagIOC|ESP|2014 Winter|1}}\n* {{flagIOC|SWE|2014 Winter|11}}\n* {{flagIOC|SUI|2014 Winter|24}}\n* {{flagIOC|UKR|2014 Winter|7}}\n* {{flagIOC|USA|2014 Winter|26}}\n{{col end}}\n\n==Controversy==\nBoth [[Canada]] and [[Slovenia]] both appealed separately to the [[Court of Arbitration for Sport]] that the three [[France|French]] athletes in the Big Final of the [[Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's ski cross|men's ski cross]] final, had their pants illegally changed by their coach. They argued it gave the three an aerodynamic advantage over the rest of the field. Both countries first appealed to the [[International Ski Federation]], but were rejected since they appealed hours after the end of the competition (when the deadline was 15 minutes after the close of the race). The appeal to the court was ultimately unsuccessful as well, because the Court agreed with the ski federation that the appeal was filed past the deadline.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Canada\u2019s skicross appeal over altered pants dismissed|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/sochi2014/2014/02/23/canadas_skicross_appeal_over_altered_pants_dismissed.html |newspaper=[[Associated Press]] |location=[[Sochi]], [[Russia]] |publisher=[[Toronto Star]] |date=23 February 2014 |accessdate= March 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n[[Alexandre Bilodeau]] became the first freestyle skiing gold medalist to defend his Olympic title, winning the men's moguls, following up his 2010 Olympics gold in men's moguls.<ref> {{cite news|url=http://www.therepublic.com/view/story/92eea089385b408c807bd32d83fe5596/OLY-FRE-Mens-Moguls |title=Canada's Alex Bilodeau takes gold in men's moguls, first two-time freestyle Olympic champion |date=10 February 2014 |newspaper=The Republic |location=Columbus, Indiana |agency=Associated Press |first=Will |last=Graves |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222153741/http://www.therepublic.com/view/story/92eea089385b408c807bd32d83fe5596/OLY-FRE-Mens-Moguls |archivedate=2014-02-22 }} </ref> [[Justine Dufour-Lapointe]] became the youngest freestyle skiing Olympic champion ever in the women's mogul event.<ref name=CTV-2014-02-08-Dufour-Lapoint-Gold-Silver>{{cite news |url= http://www.ctvnews.ca/sochi/dufour-lapointe-sisters-win-gold-and-silver-in-olympic-moguls-1.1677142 |title= Dufour-Lapointe sisters win gold and silver in Olympic moguls |publisher= CTV News |date= 8 February 2014 |author= The Canadian Press |access-date= 2014-02-17 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140209140105/http://www.ctvnews.ca/sochi/dufour-lapointe-sisters-win-gold-and-silver-in-olympic-moguls-1.1677142# |archive-date= 2014-02-09 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://digital.la84.org/digital/api/collection/p17103coll8/id/71551/download Official Results Book \u2013 Freestyle Skiing]\n\n{{Events at the 2014 Winter Olympics}}\n{{Freestyle skiing at the Winter Olympics}}\n\n[[Category:Freestyle skiing at the Winter Olympics|2014]]\n[[Category:2014 Winter Olympics events|Freestyle skiing]]\n[[Category:2014 in freestyle skiing|Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics| ]]\n[[Category:Freestyle skiing competitions in Russia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Freestyle skiing\n|games = 2014 Winter\n| image       = [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Aerials), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Halfpipe), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Moguls), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Ski Cross), Sochi 2014.png|90px]] [[File:Freestyle Skiing (Slopestyle), Sochi 2014.png|90px]]\n| caption     = Pictograms for Aerials, Halfpipe, Moguls, Ski Cross, and Slopestyle.\n|venue = [[Rosa Khutor Extreme Park]], [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]], [[Russia]]\n|dates = 6\u201321 February 2014\n|competitors = 277\n|nations = 30\n|prev = [[Freestyle skiing at the 2010 Winter Olympics|2010]]\n|next = [[Freestyle skiing at the 2018 Winter Olympics|2018]]\n}}\n{{Freestyle skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics}}\n'''[[Freestyle skiing at the Winter Olympics|Freestyle skiing]] at the [[2014 Winter Olympics]]''' was held at the [[Rosa Khutor Extreme Park]] near [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]], [[Russia]]. The ten events took place between 6\u201321 February 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/games/places/objects/mountain/snowboard/ |title=Rosa Khutor Extreme Park |publisher=[[SOOC]] |accessdate=10 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2011 the [[International Olympic Committee]] approved the addition of the halfpipe event for both, men and women.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ski halfpipe approved for 2014 Olympics |first=Olivia |last=Dwyer |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/action/freeskiing/news/story?id=6273652 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=6 April 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref> In July 2011, [[slopestyle]] was also added to the program, therefore a total of four new events were added to the freestyle skiing program.<ref>{{cite news |title=Slopestyle approved for 2014 Olympics |first=Olivia |last=Dwyer |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/action/news/story?id=6662007 |work=[[ESPN]] |date=4 July 2011 |accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Competition schedule==\n[[File:Rosa Khutor.jpg|300px|thumb|Rosa Khutor Alpine Resort, the venue for freestyle skiing]]\nThe following is the competition schedule for all ten events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/freestyle-skiing-schedule-and-results |title=Freestyle Skiing Schedule and R