ah]]\n|[[Utah Republican primary, 2008|primary, modified open]]\n|9\n|10\n|3\n|14\n|'''36'''\n|Statewide WTA<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time-blog.com/real_clear_politics/2007/11/giulianis_nomination_strategy.html |title=Giuliani's Nomination Strategy - Real Clear Politics - Mid Term Elections - Elections 2008 - TIME |publisher=Time-blog.com |date= |accessdate=2008-09-15}}</ref>\n|- align=center\n|[[West Virginia]]\n|[[West Virginia Republican caucuses, 2008|convention, modified open]]\n|9\n|10\n|3\n|8\n|'''18/30'''<ref name=\"west virginia\">West Virginia will select its eighteen at-large Delegates on February 5 at a state party convention, but then select its nine district delegates and three unpledged delegates during the party primary on Tuesday, May 13.</ref>\n|multiple ballot WTA<ref>A runoff is held amongst the top three candidates, and if no candidate receives a majority, a runoff is held amongst the top two remaining candidates, with the winner receiving all 18 at large delegates.</ref>\n|- align=center\n|colspan=2|Totals\n|'''627'''\n|'''210'''\n|'''63'''\n|'''181'''\n|'''1,069/1,081'''\n|\n|}\n\n===After Super Tuesday===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Date\n!State\n!Type\n!District-Level Delegates\n!At-Large Delegates\n!State Party Delegates\n!Bonus Delegates\n!Total Size of Delegation\n!Delegate Selection Process\n|- align=center\n|rowspan=3|February 9, 2008\n|[[Kansas]]\n|[[Kansas Republican caucuses, 2008|caucus, closed]]\n|12\n|10\n|3\n|14\n|'''39'''\n|district WTA + at-large/state party/bonus WTA<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ksgopcaucus.org/summary_delegate.htm |title=Kansas Gop Caucus :: Summary Of Delegate Selection |publisher=Ksgopcaucus.org |accessdate=2012-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211163604/http://ksgopcaucus.org/summary_delegate.htm |archive-date=2012-02-11 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|- align=center\n|[[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]]\n|[[Washington Republican caucuses, 2008|caucus]]\n|27\n|