{"title_page": "Tell Me Why (The Riddle)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Single\n| Name           = '''Tell Me Why'''\n| Cover          = Tell_me.jpg\n|type=| Artist         = [[Paul van Dyk]]\n| from Album     = Out There And Back\n| Released       = [[July 11]] [[2000]] \n| Format         = [[CD]], [[gramophone record|12\" single]]\n| Genre          = [[Electronic Dance Music|Dance]], [[Trance Music|Trance]]\n| Label          = [[Deviant Records|Deviant]], Vandit\n| Writer         = [[Paul van Dyk]], [[Sarah Cracknell]], [[Bob Stanley]], [[Pete Wiggs]]\n| Producer       = Paul van Dyk\n\n\n| Last single    = \"[[Hotel Yorba]]\"<br>(2002)\n| This single    = \"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\"<br>(2000)\n| Next single    = \"[[Columbia EP]]\"<br>(2000)\n}}\n\n'''''Tell Me Why''''' was a single released by [[Paul van Dyk]] in collaboration with the English indie dance band [[Saint Etienne (band)|Saint Etienne]], with Sarah Cracknell of the group on vocals. A Music video was made along with the song that can be found on the ''Global'' DVD.\n\n==Track Listing==\n\n===CD1===\n# Radio Mix 3:49\n# PVD Mix 8:48\n# Take A Break 6:25\n\n===CD2===\n# Vandit Mix 7:50\n# Club Mix 4:52\n# Original Mix 6:51\n\n===12\" Version - 1===\n# Vandit Mix [A]\n# Club Mix [B1]\n# Club Dub [B2]\n\n===12\" Version - 2===\n# Original Mix [A]\n# Take A Break Mix [B1]\n# Take A Break Dub [B2]\n\n\n{{2000s-electronic-album-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2000 albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2012}}\n{{Refimprove|date=November 2006}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\n| cover      = Tell Me Why (The Riddle) cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Paul van Dyk]] featuring [[Saint Etienne (band)|Saint Etienne]]\n| album      = [[Out There and Back]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2000|7|11|df=y}}\n| format     = [[CD single|CD]], [[12-inch single|12\"]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Trance music|Trance]]\n| length     = 3:49\n| label      = [[Vandit]] ([[Germany]]) - <small>156 871</small><br>[[Deviant Records|Deviant]] ([[United Kingdom|UK]])- <small>DVNT36</small><br>[[Mute Records|Mute]] ([[United States|U.S.]]) - <small>9129</small>\n| writer     = [[Paul van Dyk]], [[Sarah Cracknell]], [[Bob Stanley (musician)|Bob Stanley]], [[Pete Wiggs]]\n| producer   = Paul van Dyk\n| chronology = [[Paul van Dyk]]\n| prev_title = Another Way/Avenue\n| prev_year  = 1999\n| next_title = We Are Alive\n| next_year  = 2000\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Saint Etienne (band)|Saint Etienne]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = How We Used to Live\n | prev_year  = 2000\n | title      = Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\n | year       = 2000\n | next_title = Heart Failed (In the Back of a Taxi)\n | next_year  = 2000\n}}\n{{Audio sample\n | type        = single\n | file        = Paul Van Dyk - Tell Me Why (The Riddle).ogg\n | description = \"Paul Van Dyk - Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\"\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Tell Me Why (The Riddle)'''\" is a song released by [[Paul van Dyk]] in collaboration with English indie dance band [[Saint Etienne (band)|Saint Etienne]], with [[Sarah Cracknell]] of the group on vocals.<ref>{{citation|title=Van Dyk's 'Out There' Soul On Mute|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=24 June 2000|author=Michael Paoletta}}</ref> A music video (filmed 28 May 2000) was made along with the song that can be found on the ''Global'' DVD.\n\nPeaking at number seven on the [[UK Singles Chart]], it remains the highest charting single on the chart for both artists to date.\n\n==Track listing==\n\n===<small>CD: Deviant / DVNT36CDS (UK)</small>===\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Radio Mix) - 3:49</small>\n\n'''<small>Continuous-mixed tracks:</small>'''\n# <li value=\"2\"><small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (PvD Mix) - 8:49</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Take a Break) - 6:26</small>\n\n===<small>CD: Deviant / DVNT36CDR (UK)</small>===\n# \"<small>Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Vandit Mix) - 7:50</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Mix) - 4:52</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Original Mix) - 6:51</small>\n\n===<small>CD: Vandit / 156 871-2 (Germany)</small>===\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Radio Mix) - 3:49</small>\n\n'''<small>Continuous-mixed tracks:</small>'''\n# <li value=\"2\"><small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Vandit Mix) - 7:49</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Mix) - 4:52</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (PvD Mix) - 8:20</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Take a Break) - 6:09</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Original Mix) - 8:07</small>\n\n*<small>also released in the US (Mute / 9129-2)</small>\n\n===<small>CD: Avex / AVTCDS-253 (Hong Kong)</small>===\n'''<small>Unedited remixes:</small>'''\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Radio Mix) - 3:49</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Vandit Mix) - 8:03</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (PvD Mix) - 9:26</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Take a Break) - 6:39</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Mix) - 5:54</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Original Mix) - 8:44</small>\n\n'''<small>Continuous-mixed tracks:</small>'''\n# <li value=\"7\"><small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Vandit Mix) - 7:49</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Mix) - 4:52</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (PvD Mix) - 8:21</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Take a Break) - 6:09</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Original Mix) - 8:07</small>\n\n===<small>12\": Deviant / DVNT36X (UK)</small>===\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Vandit Mix) - 8:03</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Mix) - 5:53</small>\n#<small>\"Tell Me Why (The Riddle)\" (Club Dub) - 5:53</small>\n\n==='''''12\": Deviant / DVNT36XR (UK)'''''===\n\n#<small>\"Tell Me 